Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/miles-mcguire/vimfiles.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:
    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vim

Switch to '~/.vim' and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update

NOTE! Command-T native C extensions may (read: will) need to be rebuilt. First make sure the vim build in question has Ruby support enabled, then go to the the 'ruby/command-t/' directory and 'ruby extconf.rb' and run make on the resultant makefile
